    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_aftæ" xml:lang="os-x-iron">
                <form xml:id="form_d3903e66" type="lemma"><orth>aftæ</orth></form>
                <usg><lang/></usg>
                <sense xml:id="sense_d3903e72"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>так</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>this way</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3903e84">
                        <quote>aftæ fæzæǧy jæxīcæn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>так он говорит себе</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>so he tells himself</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>16</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3903e103">
                        <quote>tærqūs-læppynyl aftæ ma fæxūd</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>не смейся так над зайчонком</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>don't laugh at the bunny like that</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>107</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3903e122">
                        <quote>aftæ ræsuǧd wyd xalaǧūd…</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>так красив был шатер…</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the tent was so beautiful…</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭп."/><biblScope>16</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3903e141">
                        <quote>ūj bakodta aftæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>он так и сделал</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>he did so</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭ"/><biblScope>I 20</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3903e160">
                        <quote>Wyryzmæg fīdīwægæn nyqqærkænyn kodta aftæ…</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Урузмаг велел герольду прокричать так…</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Uruzmag told the herald to shout like this…</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОТ"/><biblScope>72</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d3903e180">
                        <quote>aftætæ kodtoj ūcy ræstæǵy xīcæwttæ æmæ barǵyntæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>так поступали в то время господа и власть имущие</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>so did the gentlemen and those in power at that time</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>63</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Образовалось из %iа%i + %iūtæ%i (для звукового перехода ср.
                        <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3903e202" xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>завтра</w></mentioned>). В текстах, изданных
                            <bibl><author>Шифнером</author></bibl>(1868), мы встречаем еще форму
                    %iautæ%i рядом с %iaftæ%i: стр. 8, пословица № 41 (<mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e339" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e210" xml:lang="os-x-iron"><lang/>
                        <w>bælas aūtæ zægyj…</w></mentioned>), стр. 9, пословица № 54 (<mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e344" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e215" xml:lang="os-x-iron"><lang/>
                        <w>… autæ ænqælyj</w></mentioned>) и др. A. <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Шегрен"/></bibl>(1844) дает %iaute%i, %iavte%i и %iafte%i.
                    Предположение %sHübschmann%s'a (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>62</biblScope></bibl>) и
                    %sGauthiot%s (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_MSL"/><biblScope>XX
                            10</biblScope></bibl>) что <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e361" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e232" xml:lang="os-x-iron"><lang/>
                        <w>aftæ</w></mentioned> и <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e366" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e237" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/>
                        <w>otæ</w></mentioned> восходят оба к <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e371" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e242" xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>avaθa</w></mentioned> и (<bibl><author>Gauthiot</author></bibl>) отражают
                    два акцентуальных варианта древнеиранского слова (<mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e376" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e251" xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>àvᵃθa</w></mentioned> и <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e382" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e256" xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>ᵃvàθa</w></mentioned>) не имеет под собой никакой почвы; д. %iо%i в
                        <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e387" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e261" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/>
                        <w>otæ</w></mentioned> представляет закономерное стяжение группы %iava%i,
                    тогда как и. %iaf%i в <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e392" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e266" xml:lang="os-x-iron"><lang/>
                        <w>aftæ</w></mentioned> ни при каких акцентуальных условиях не может
                    восходить к %iava%i, , не говоря уже о том, что допущение двух ударений для
                    древнеиранского совершенно произвольно. Из <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e397" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e271" xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>*àvaθa</w></mentioned> так же мало могло получиться %iaft-%i, как из
                        <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e402" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e276" xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>*nàvaka</w></mentioned> — *%inavg%i (см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_nog"/>). Сближение
                        <bibl><author>Benveniste</author></bibl><mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e410" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e286" xml:lang="os-x-iron"><lang/>
                        <w>aftæ</w></mentioned> с <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e415" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e291" xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>āpat</w>
                        <gloss><q>хорошо</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Gramm._sogd."/><biblScope>II 179</biblScope></bibl>) также
                    сомнительно. В отношении наращения одного указательного местоимения (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_a"/>) на другое (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_ū"/>) ср. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e431" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e308" xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>a-sau-</w></mentioned> или <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e437" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e313" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/>
                        <w>awæxæn</w>
                        <gloss><q>такой</q></gloss></mentioned> из %ia+wæ+xæn%i, где %iwæn%i равно
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ū"/> в %ia+ū+tæ%i → %iaftæ%i. См. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_aftæmæj"/>. Сюда же, по-видимому, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_aftid"/> ‘пустой’.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">The word is derived from %iа%i + %iūtæ%i (for the sound
                    transition cf. <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d3903e331" xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>zavtra</w></mentioned>). We also find another form %iautæ%i apart from
                    %iaftæ%i in the text published by <bibl><author>Schiffner</author></bibl>(1868):
                    p. 8, saying № 41 (<mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e210" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e339" xml:lang="os-x-iron"><lang/>
                        <w>bælas aūtæ zægyj…</w></mentioned>), p. 9, saying № 54 (<mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e215" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e344" xml:lang="os-x-iron"><lang/>
                        <w>… autæ ænqælyj</w></mentioned>), etc. A. <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Шегрен"/></bibl> (1844) gives %iaute%i, %iavte%i and
                    %iafte%i. The assumption of %sHübschmann%s (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>62</biblScope></bibl>) and
                    %sGauthiot%s (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_MSL"/><biblScope>XX
                            10</biblScope></bibl>) that <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e232" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e361" xml:lang="os-x-iron"><lang/>
                        <w>aftæ</w></mentioned> and <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e237" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e366" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/>
                        <w>otæ</w></mentioned> both trace back to <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e242" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e371" xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>avaθa</w></mentioned> and (according to %sGauthiot%s) represent two
                    accentual variants of an Old Iranian word (<mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e251" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e376" xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>àvᵃθa</w></mentioned> and <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e256" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e382" xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>ᵃvàθa</w></mentioned>) is not supported by any evidence; Digor %iо%i in
                        <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e261" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e387" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/>
                        <w>otæ</w></mentioned> is a regular contraction of the group %iava%i while
                    Iron %iaf%i in <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e266" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e392" xml:lang="os-x-iron"><lang/>
                        <w>aftæ</w></mentioned> can under no accentual conditions trace back to
                    %iava%i, not to mention that the assumption of a double stressed word in Old
                    Iranian is completely arbitrary. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e271" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e397" xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>*àvaθa</w></mentioned> could hardly be the source for %iaft-%i, as well
                    as <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e276" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e402" xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/>
                        <w>*nàvaka</w></mentioned> could be the source for *%inavg%i (see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_nog"/>). It is also doubtful to connect <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e286" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e410" xml:lang="os-x-iron"><lang/>
                        <w>aftæ</w></mentioned> with <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e291" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e415" xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>āpat</w>
                        <gloss><q>good</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Gramm._sogd."/><biblScope>II 179</biblScope></bibl>), as
                    did %sBenveniste%s. As for the augmentation of one demonstrative pronoun (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_a"/>) with another (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_ū"/>), cf. <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e308" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e431" xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>a-sau-</w></mentioned> or <mentioned corresp="#mentioned_d3903e313" xml:id="mentioned_d3903e437" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/>
                        <w>awæxæn</w>
                        <gloss><q>such</q></gloss></mentioned> from %ia+wæ+xæn%i, where %iwæn%i
                    equals <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ū"/> in %ia+ū+tæ%i → %iaftæ%i. See <ref type="xr" target="#entry_aftæmæj"/>. Probably <ref type="xr" target="#entry_aftid"/> ‘empty’ should also be included here.</etym>
            </entry>
